(3) Since \mathbb {L}_{1}\subseteq \mathbb {L}_{1}\mathbb {L}_{2} and \mathbb {L}_{2}\subseteq \mathbb {L}_{1}\mathbb {L}_{2}, we have \mathop {	extrm {Aut}}
olimits _{\mathbb {F}}(\Bbbk / \mathbb {L}_{1}\mathbb {L}_{2})\subseteq H_{1}\cap H_{2}. Conversely, if \sigma \in H_{1}\cap H_{2}, it fixes \mathbb {L}_{1} and \mathbb {L}_{2}. Since \mathbb {L}_{1}\mathbb {L}_{2} is generated by \mathbb {L}_{1} and \mathbb {L}_{2} over \mathbb {F}, \sigma also fixes \mathbb {L}_{1}\mathbb {L}_{2}. Then H_{1}\cap H_{2}\subseteq \mathop {	extrm {Aut}}
olimits _{\mathbb {F}}(\Bbbk / \mathbb {L}_{1}\mathbb {L}_{2}). Therefore \mathop {	extrm {Gal}}
olimits (\Bbbk / \mathbb {L}_{1}\mathbb {L}_{2})=H_{1}\cap H_{2}, which establishes the first claim of (3).

(3) Since \mathbb {L}_{1}\subseteq \mathbb {L}_{1}\mathbb {L}_{2} and \mathbb {L}_{2}\subseteq \mathbb {L}_{1}\mathbb {L}_{2}, we have \mathop {	extrm {Aut}}
olimits _{\mathbb {F}}(\Bbbk / \mathbb {L}_{1}\mathbb {L}_{2})\subseteq H_{1}\cap H_{2}. Conversely, if \sigma \in H_{1}\cap H_{2}, it fixes \mathbb {L}_{1} and \mathbb {L}_{2}. Since \mathbb {L}_{1}\mathbb {L}_{2} is generated by \mathbb {L}_{1} and \mathbb {L}_{2} over \mathbb {F}, \sigma also fixes \mathbb {L}_{1}\mathbb {L}_{2}. Then H_{1}\cap H_{2}\subseteq \mathop {	extrm {Aut}}
olimits _{\mathbb {F}}(\Bbbk / \mathbb {L}_{1}\mathbb {L}_{2}). Therefore \mathop {	extrm {Gal}}
olimits (\Bbbk / \mathbb {L}_{1}\mathbb {L}_{2})=H_{1}\cap H_{2}, which establishes the first claim of (3).
